text: John Welles (by 1485 – 1515/18), of New Windsor, Berkshire, was an English politician. He was a Member (MP) of the Parliament of England for New Windsor in 1510, 1512 and 1515. ==References== Category:15th-century births Category:1510s deaths Category:Members of the Parliament of England (pre-1707) for New Windsor Category:English MPs 1510 Category:English MPs 1512–1514 Category:English MPs 1515
